{
  "name": "Healthy Lemon Protein Bars",
  "description": "Frosted no-bake lemon bars tuned to a sub-10 cal:protein ratio for the no-bake / protein-bar format. Oat-forward almond+oat protein cookie layer (leaning carbs over fat) pressed in a loaf pan, bound with a real+sugar-free maple blend (a little real maple for workout carbs) and applesauce in place of most of the butter; topped with a whisked 0% Greek yogurt / cream-cheese lemon frosting set with a little sugar-free vanilla pudding (no blender, no cottage-cheese clumps). Cut from the original 13.7 ratio while keeping it a real frosted bar, not a protein brick. Same frosted-bar format as the Cookie Dough and Peppermint bars.",
  "tags": [
    "protein",
    "lemon",
    "frosted",
    "no-bake",
    "bars"
  ],
  "yield": {
    "amount": 8,
    "unit": "bars"
  },
  "content": {
    "steps": [
      {
        "componentKey": "b1",
        "order": 1,
        "section": "cookie layer",
        "instructionText": "Mix the protein powder, almond flour, oat flour, melted butter, both maple syrups (real + sugar-free), applesauce, and lemon juice into a stiff dough. Press very firmly into a parchment-lined loaf pan; chill while you make the frosting."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "f1",
        "order": 2,
        "section": "frosting",
        "instructionText": "Whisk the Greek yogurt, cream cheese, lemon juice, pudding mix, and Splenda smooth - no blender needed, the yogurt is already smooth - then stir in the protein powder until thick and spreadable. Spread over the cookie layer; it firms as it chills."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "z1",
        "order": 3,
        "section": "set",
        "instructionText": "Freeze ~20 min until set, then slice into 8 bars."
      }
    ],
