    "notes": [
      {
        "componentKey": "n1",
        "kind": "technique",
        "stepKey": "b1",
        "text": "Press the cookie layer very firmly - it's oat-forward with no egg and no bake, binding from the maple syrup, applesauce, and just 1 tbsp butter. A loose press crumbles when sliced: pack it down hard and chill until firm before frosting. If the dough feels dry, work in a teaspoon of milk or applesauce."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n2",
        "kind": "technique",
        "stepKey": "f1",
        "text": "Greek yogurt sets looser than blended cottage, so the tablespoon of pudding mix is what firms the frosting - don't skip it, and use a thick Greek (Fage 0%). If it still seems loose, chill it 10 minutes before spreading."
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n4",
        "kind": "technique",
        "text": "If the frosting is too loose after adding the 30g protein, add cream cheese a tablespoon at a time rather than more protein — extra protein powder can make the layer gummy after freezing.",
        "stepKey": "f1"
      },
      {
        "componentKey": "n5",
        "kind": "pitfall",
        "text": "Freeze 20 min to set, then move to the fridge — bars left in the freezer too long become rock-hard and the white-chocolate frosting can crack when sliced. Temper 5 min at room temp before cutting if frozen solid.",
        "stepKey": "z1"
      }
    ]
  }
